&lt;p&gt;Now,&amp;nbsp;arranging it in reverse order,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Left End ! ? T * R X @ ^ G D % # * Z N $ &amp;amp; Right End&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;third element from the left end is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;T.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;fourth to the right of&amp;nbsp;T is&lt;strong&gt; @.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, &lt;strong&gt;@&lt;/strong&gt; is fourth to the right of third element from the left end.&lt;/p&gt;
Hence, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;option 1&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.

&lt;p&gt;The logic followed here is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total overs of the match = 50 overs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; The chasing team&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;scored 5 runs per over in the first 30 overs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; Runs scored by chasing team until 30 overs = 5&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 30&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; Runs scored by chasing team until 30 overs =&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;150 runs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; Required run rate is 10 runs per over.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; Remaining overs of the match = 20 overs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; Runs need to score by the chasing team to win the match = 10&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 20&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; Runs need to score by the chasing team to win the match = 200 runs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total runs need to score by the chasing team to win the match&amp;nbsp;= 150 + 200&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;there4;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Total runs need to score by the chasing team to win the match&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 350 runs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The score of the first team will be = Runs needed by the chasing team to win the match - 1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The score of the first team will be = 350 - 1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The score of the first team will be = 349&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;349&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

